<SUMMARY>
This model computes the utility of accepting an offer by first deriving a fairness reference from token allocation and combined earnings. The utility equals the offered split adjusted by a logarithmic bonus if the offer exceeds fairness or by a penalty if it falls short—with two learnable parameters governing the bonus (tau_param) and penalty (lambda_param) effects.
</SUMMARY>
